example.code:
private void toolStripButton2_Click( object sender, EventArgs e )
{
    if ( !webControl.IsLive )
        return;

    webControl.GoForward();
}

member.summary:
Gets or sets the parent window for this  instance. This is only valid
for windowed  instances (see ),
on the Windows platform.

member.example:
The following example illustrates handling the  event in a WPF application that uses
 controls. In this example, we create a ChildWindow window
that hosts a . This window and its hosted 
will be used to wrap and present the child view passed to , or navigate to the
